{"article_id":"aMgshXd3QoJLflIQ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As of Saturday afternoon , more than 35 inches of rain had fallen in Surf City on the North Carolina coast .","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"That ' s an enormous amount of water","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to fall in two days .","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"And the flooding isn ' t over .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Florence made landfall in North Carolina on Friday morning near Wilmington as a hurricane ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"and then slowed down to a sluggish 2 miles per hour .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"It essentially stalled over the Carolinas ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"bringing incredible amounts of rain to the region .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"Even though it was downgraded to a tropical storm and , now , a tropical depression ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"the danger","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"it poses","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"in terms of flooding","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"is far from over ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"as floodwaters continue to fill rivers inland .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"\" As the moisture with Florence moves into the Appalachians ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"expect more flash flooding and possible landslides , \"","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"the National Weather Service warned Saturday afternoon .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Local authorities have reported at least 14 deaths","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"related from the storm so far .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"though the rain is slowly making its way out of the region ,","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"conditions on the ground still continue to be dangerous in many places .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"The flooding WILL GET WORSE in many locations across SC , NC and VA.","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"River levels will continue to rise today and early this week .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"If you live near a body of water ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"do n't let your guard down","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"and follow local evacuation orders !","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"https : //t.co/nHwnCyIDa8","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"pic.twitter.com/oNwHdcQtE","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"4 - NWS","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"( @ NWS )","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"September 16 , 2018","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"The NWS is called the flooding \" catastrophic. \"","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"In all , forecasters estimate","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"that 18 trillion gallons of water may drop on the region .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Here ' s what we know about the flooding","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"still to come","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"and why this is shaping up to be a very costly natural disaster .","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"As the storm crept from North Carolina to South Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"it dumped a truly enormous amount of rain ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"breaking records .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Swansboro North Carolina saw more than 30 inches .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"That ' s a record amount ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"6 inches greater","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"than the city saw with Hurricane Floyd in 1999 .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"These numbers make Florence comparable to last year ' s Hurricane Harvey ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"which stalled over the Houston area","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and broke the national rainfall record for a single tropical storm .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"It dumped around 27 trillion gallons of water in total","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and destroyed around 30,000 homes .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"40-50 '' rainfall totals beginning to show up in higher-res guidance","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"as the event begins to unfold .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Reminds me of how guidance began to respond in Harvey .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Regardless of exact totals ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"rainfall will be exceptional","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and flooding catastrophic .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"pic.","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"twitter.com/y7gv3HTh4R","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"- Taylor Trogdon","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"( @ TTrogdon )","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"September 14 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Track where the storm goes from here with this map","depth":4},{"id":62,"text":"that pulls in the latest forecast from the National Hurricane Center .","depth":4},{"id":63,"text":"All the rain means there ' s a lot of potential flooding over a huge area .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"And it ' s not just happening on the coasts .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"As the storm progresses","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"and the heavy rain continues to fall ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"rivers and creeks further inland will start to overflow as well .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Not helping :","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"The fact","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"that the ground in the Carolinas is already saturated from a storm-filled summer .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"That will lead to more surface runoff inland .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"For instance , the Cape Fear River in Fayetteville , North Carolina , is about 100 miles from the coast .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"It ' s expected to flood more than 27 feet above its banks .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"\" Life-threatening , catastrophic flash floods and prolonged significant river flooding are likely over portions of the Carolinas and the southern to central Appalachians from western North Carolina into west-central Virginia and far eastern West Virginia through early next week , \"","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"the weather service warned Saturday ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"adding","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that landslides are possible in the mountains .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"This flooding also poses an environmental risk .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"According to the Associated Press ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"2,000 cubic yards of coal ash","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"- a byproduct of coal power production -","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"were washed away from a landfill near Wilmington , North Carolina .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Coal ash includes toxic substances like mercury and arsenic ,","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"which can now flow into rivers , lakes , and the ocean .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"The last 2 high tides in Wilmington , NC have been in the top 10 highest water levels on record at our tide gauge .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"The next high tide is at 4 p.m.","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Water is causing flooding","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"& will likely remain elevated through early next week .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Find real-time water levels :","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"https : //t.co/Uh3VniZjeI","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"pic.twitter.com/ciLVknhYUy","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"- NOAA 's Ocean Service","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"( @ noaaocean )","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"September 16 , 2018","depth":2},{"id":95,"text":"This storm is impacting 5 million people .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"1 million are without power .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"Over a dozen people have already died .","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"About 5 million people throughout the region will see 10 inches of rain or more over the next few days ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"the NHC predicted last week ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"covering an area hundreds of miles wide","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"and including the cities of Wilmington , Fayetteville , Charlotte , Myrtle Beach , and many others .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"The southeastern-most areas of North Carolina will see the worst of it ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"where accumulations greater than 20 inches are predicted .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Duke Energy , a power utility","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"that services North and South Carolina ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"estimates","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"1 to 3 million people could be without electricity due to the storm ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"and that it could take weeks to restore it all .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Already , more than a million are without power , mostly in North Carolina .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"Statewide power outage total at 9:30 am is 814,351 with the highest concentration in New Hanover , Brunswick , Columbus , Craven , Duplin , Onslow , Carteret , Cumberland , Moore , Robeson , Sampson , Wake counties .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Get updates :","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"https : //t.co/Yx3twhyOqj","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"- NC Emergency Managem","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"( @ NCEmergency )","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"September 15 , 2018","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Emergency responders and volunteers have had to rescue hundreds of people from their homes in New Bern , North Carolina .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"And the wind , rain , and floods have claimed several lives , including an infant .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"WPD can confirm the first two fatalities of Hurricane # Florence in Wilmington .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"A mother and infant were killed","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"when a tree fell on their house .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"The father was transported to NHRMC with injuries .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"https : //t.co/FC5PAhuxig","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"- Wilmington Police","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"( @ WilmingtonPD )","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"September 14 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"Other deaths ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"the Charlotte Observer reports ,","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"include a person","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"electrocuted","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"trying to operate a power generator ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"and a woman","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"who died of a heart attack","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"waiting for rescue crews to reach her .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"A preliminary assessment from Stony Brook University modeled the forecast of Florence","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"but also imagined what would have happened in a world","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"that hadn ' t been artificially warmed up by greenhouse gas emissions .","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"In short ,","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"they concluded ,","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"the warmer atmosphere","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"we live in today","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"allowed Florence to dump 50 percent more rainfall .","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"In the months to come , climate scientists will more carefully and painstakingly conduct climate change attribution studies","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"to confirm or amend this result .","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"( Over this past year , climate scientists have now determined via two separate research efforts","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"that Hurricane Harvey ' s record-blasting rains were likely amplified by climate change . )","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"But we don ' t need these studies","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"to know","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"that climate change has already had an impact .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"As the Washington Post reported Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"\" Some six inches of the coming storm surge is attributable to climate change","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"because sea levels have risen in the past 100 years or so. \"","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"If this same exact storm had hit","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"before seas levels had risen ,","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"it would not be able to push as much water inland .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":309,"left":248,"right":308,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":215,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":189,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nu